{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/writing-guide/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"hoodie"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"0601b249-0ae6-5744-9ae0-1f2ec6c884f4","excerpt":"1. Add a post You can add posts by creating a new markdown document in the  path. 1-1. Post file structure There are two ways to add a new document. The firstâ€¦","html":"<h2>1. Add a post</h2>\n<p>You can add posts by creating a new markdown document in the <code class=\"language-text\">contents/post</code> path.</p>\n<h3>1-1. Post file structure</h3>\n<p>There are two ways to add a new document. The first is to create a markdown file for a single document without a directory. If you are writing about JavaScript, you can create a <code class=\"language-text\">about-javascript.md</code> file in the <code class=\"language-text\">contents/posts</code> directory.</p>\n<p>The second is to create a directory and create an <code class=\"language-text\">index.md</code> file in it. This method is useful when the document contains several additional files such as picture files.</p>\n<p>Each file name or directory name becomes a unique address of the document and can be accessed as follows. <code class=\"language-text\">https://siteURL/about-javascript</code>.</p>\n<h3>1-2. Frontmatter</h3>\n<p>The Markdown document you create contains the document's metadata called frontmatter.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">---\ntitle: &quot;ðŸ¤” 3. Writing Guide&quot;\ndescription: &quot;How to write and add a post?&quot;\ndate: 2021-05-03\nupdate: 2021-05-03\ntags:\n  - hoodie\n  - writing-guide\nseries: &quot;Getting started your blog with gatsby-starter-hoodie&quot;\n---</code></pre></div>\n<p>Above is the frontmatter of the document you are currently reading. Among them, title and date are required. It is recommended to enclose the string with spaces in quotation marks.</p>\n<h3>1-3. Writing markdown</h3>\n<p>If you have written a Frontmatter, you can write your markdown document under it. gatsby-starter-hoodie supports most Markdown syntax. To learn more about Markdown syntax, see the <a href=\"https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/\">Mastering Markdown</a> documentation on GitHub.</p>\n<h2>2. Syntax Highlighting &#x26; Katex</h2>\n<h3>2-1. Syntax Highlighting</h3>\n<p>Syntax highlighting based on Prism.JS is supported.</p>\n<h4>Examples</h4>\n<p>Javascript</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\"><pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello, world!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Python</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Hello, world!\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>It supports a wider variety of other languages. Check it out on the <a href=\"https://prismjs.com/\">Prism.js website</a>.</p>\n<h3>2-2. Katex</h3>\n<p>It supports Katex syntax, you can easily express complex formulas.</p>\n<h4>Inline mode</h4>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E = m c^{2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">c</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<h4>Block mode</h4>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mo>âˆ«</mo><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">âˆž</mi></msubsup><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\int_{0}^{\\infty} f(x) dx</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:2.326242em;vertical-align:-0.9119499999999999em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol large-op\" style=\"margin-right:0.44445em;position:relative;top:-0.0011249999999999316em;\">âˆ«</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.414292em;\"><span style=\"top:-1.7880500000000001em;margin-left:-0.44445em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.8129000000000004em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">âˆž</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">â€‹</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.9119499999999999em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">d</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span></span></span></span></span>\n<h2>3. Add images to a post</h2>\n<p>You can easily embed images using relative paths. It is easy to manage documents containing images by creating a directory.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/aaf92/sample-image.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.1764705882353%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"sample image\"\n        title=\"sample image\"\n        src=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/a22ce/sample-image.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/0b705/sample-image.jpg 170w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/31389/sample-image.jpg 340w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/a22ce/sample-image.jpg 680w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/29373/sample-image.jpg 1020w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/232dc/sample-image.jpg 1360w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/69b244095d8c72158c9dd2d4ca59a7b1/aaf92/sample-image.jpg 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Images are loaded with Lazy Loading, so you can secure fast document loading speed.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>âš  The extension of the file must be set to lowercase.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>4. Tagging</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/6031b/tag-example.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 18.823529411764707%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"tag example\"\n        title=\"tag example\"\n        src=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/a22ce/tag-example.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/0b705/tag-example.jpg 170w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/31389/tag-example.jpg 340w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/a22ce/tag-example.jpg 680w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/82ce4bec7f5360eef32a473171b181af/6031b/tag-example.jpg 737w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can classify and search documents by tag set in Frontmatter. All tags you set can be viewed and searched in <code class=\"language-text\">https://siteUrl/tags</code>.</p>\n<h2>5. Series</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 677px; margin-bottom: 1rem;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/1ea4e56966cb5fb6e110d32124fd883c/d1584/series-example.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 17.058823529411764%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"series example\"\n        title=\"series example\"\n        src=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/1ea4e56966cb5fb6e110d32124fd883c/d1584/series-example.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/1ea4e56966cb5fb6e110d32124fd883c/0b705/series-example.jpg 170w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/1ea4e56966cb5fb6e110d32124fd883c/31389/series-example.jpg 340w,\n/gatsby-starter-hoodie/static/1ea4e56966cb5fb6e110d32124fd883c/d1584/series-example.jpg 677w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can publish multiple related documents in a series. The series set in Frontmatter is grouped together and shown at the top of the document. This can be useful for serialized documents with an order. Series documents are displayed in ascending order of creation date.</p>\n<p>The current document is also set in a series called <code class=\"language-text\">Getting started your blog with gatsby-starter-hoodie</code>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸ¤” 3. Writing Guide","date":"May 03, 2021","update":"May 03, 2021","tags":["hoodie","writing-guide"],"series":"Getting started your blog with gatsby-starter-hoodie"},"fields":{"slug":"/writing-guide/","readingTime":{"minutes":2.215}}},"seriesList":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"dcc82d0b-d5ad-5735-ba6b-bb75555ffe9e","fields":{"slug":"/about-hoodie/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸŽ‡ 1. About gatsby-starter-hoodie"}}},{"node":{"id":"5298c46e-d923-5071-8e5a-f73df8ff3321","fields":{"slug":"/quick-start/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸš€ 2. Quick Start"}}},{"node":{"id":"0601b249-0ae6-5744-9ae0-1f2ec6c884f4","fields":{"slug":"/writing-guide/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸ¤” 3. Writing Guide"}}},{"node":{"id":"5ea70ea9-008b-517e-9575-89071bfc5f11","fields":{"slug":"/other-tips/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸ¤© 4. Other Tips"}}}]},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/quick-start/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸš€ 2. Quick Start"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/other-tips/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ðŸ¤© 4. Other Tips"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"0601b249-0ae6-5744-9ae0-1f2ec6c884f4","series":"Getting started your blog with gatsby-starter-hoodie","previousPostId":"5298c46e-d923-5071-8e5a-f73df8ff3321","nextPostId":"5ea70ea9-008b-517e-9575-89071bfc5f11"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}